page.title: 11S'gate/The Green cont'd
page.content: {Transport:} Although 90% of the population have cars, the area is well served by public transport. London Regional Transport operates frequent buses in the area. The area is also fortunate in possessing 'local' bus W9 (Enfield-Muswell Hill). This service stops at any point on request. LRT have recently sold the route to Eastern National as part of the cuts programme. There is also a railway station (Palmers Green) which is on BR Eastern Region's Hertford North to Moorgate Line. This is well used by local commuters.
